<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Australian sauce and dressing brand Praise has released a new range of flavoured mayonnaises, including a chicken salt option that's causing a stir among hot chip enthusiasts. </p>

<p>The $4 bottle of sweet and salty mayo, which dropped alongside smokey BBQ, chilli jam and a beetroot style option, claims to be 'chickeney, salty and creamy'.</p>

<p>But there has been a mixed reaction from mayo lovers, particularly those who say this sauce will encourage foodies to 'drown' their potatoes in mayonnaise.</p>

<p>The $4 bottle of sweet and salty mayo, which dropped alongside smokey BBQ, chilli jam and a beetroot style option, claims to be 'chickeney, salty and creamy'</p>

<p>But there has been a mixed reaction from mayo lovers, particularly those who say this sauce will encourage foodies to 'drown' their potatoes in mayonnaise</p>

<p>'You're only meant to dip your chips in mayo, not completely cover them like you would with chicken salt,' said one person on Instagram.</p>

<p>'I'm not sure this will taste as good as I want it too,' said another.</p>

